    <body>
      <head>Victor (Viktor) Klingmüller (Klingmueller)</head>
      <div>

        <p>German(?) violinist and teacher, friend of <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard
          Oppel</ref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>Victor Klingmüller was teacher of violin at the <ref cRef="entity-002608">Kiel
            Conservatory</ref>(?). He performed a number of <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard
            Oppel</ref>’s compositions for violin. Oppel also entrusted the third son of his third
          marriage, <ref cRef="entity-008510">Hans Reinhard Oppel</ref>, on occasions when he was
          away from <ref cRef="entity-002757">Kiel</ref>.</p>

        <p>(Information about Klingmüller is very scarce. It is likely that Volker Klingmüller (born
          Kiel, 1909) was a son: he studied with Reinhard Oppel in Kiel and Leipzig, presumably in
          the early 1930s, and was an amateur viola player.)</p>
      </div>

